  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n[`OVM_L1ETHGateway.sol`](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/master/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/bridge/tokens/OVM_L1ETHGateway.sol) accepts ETH deposits from users when it should only accept deposits from `Proxy__OVM_L1ETHGateway`.\r\n\r\nYou can see that people were able to make deposits to `OVM_L1ETHGateway` on Kovan when you look at [the balance of the contract on etherscan](https://kovan.etherscan.io/address/0x0E8917aF9eB7812c7819EF4e80D2217679d11324). The last deposit was made on 4/21/2021 at 8:51:56.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n`Proxy__OVM_L1ETHGateway` should be the only contract able to make deposit calls to `OVM_L1ETHGateway`.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThis issue was surfaced after a discord member pointed out that in our integration docs, we recommend using `OVM_L1ETHGateway` to deposit ETH to L2, an issue that will be fixed in it's own PR in [community-hub](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/community-hub/pulls)",
