    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So, we could do the opposite of this to prevent direct calls to the contract (h/t @frangio):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/Uniswap/uniswap-v3-core/blob/e3589b192d0be27e100cd0daaf6c97204fdb1899/contracts/NoDelegateCall.sol#L10-L20\r\n\r\nIt's not hard to include, and probably not that expensive (the address is stored as a constant). But then also:\r\n\r\n> we've heard of people putting this protection measure in place, but i don't think i had ever heard of someone actually making that mistake\r\n\r\n- @frangio\r\n\r\n> a fix on the docs is definitely easier than one in the contracts\r\n\r\n- @spalladino\r\n\r\nDo we know how that address got into the docs, how likely is this to happen again? I'm assuming it was read from a regenesis file somewhere, which does feel like an easy enough mistake to make. ",
